            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add the <strong>cooked potatoes</strong> to one side of a baking tray (or two!) and drizzle over the <strong>sage oil </strong>(reserve the pan)</p><p>Add the<strong> chopped parsnip </strong>and<strong> carrot </strong>to the other side of the tray[s]<strong> </strong>with a knob of <strong>butter alternative </strong>and a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and <strong>pepper</strong> and put the tray[s] in the oven for an initial 15 min</p><p>After 15 min, add the <strong>Brussels sprouts </strong>to the tray[s] with a knob of <strong>butter alternative</strong> and return to the oven for a further 15 min or until the potatoes are crispy – these are your <strong>sage</strong> <strong>roast potatoes </strong>and<strong> roasted vegetables</strong></p>",
      "order": 6,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-6-1665139852550-x200.jpg",
